                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2005-05-24</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Kudos to Crichton for writing an entertaining and educational book.  One has to ask whether scientists and people involved in such causes ignore many of the facts presented to them in favor of seeing things the way they want them to be.  This book is what all good books should be:  you learn something you didn't know, you question things you didn't question before, and you become more vigilent to the way information is presented to you in the future.  Having read all of Crighton's books before, I do find he mixes science and adventure very well, and it certainly is an exciting ride along the way.  He also has good information after the book that is often as interesting as the book itself.  I do recommend this book (highly) as well as everything else he has ever written.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Please ask yourself...</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>1</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
